The paper deals with encrypted data structures and their security, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The data structure is designed for efficient search and retrieval of data, which is a common problem in database management systems (cs.DB). The logarithmic-time search and linear space complexity suggest that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions retrofitting the indices to existing database management systems, which suggests that it may fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper presents a provably secure solution, which may suggest that it falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
